    <!-- About Text Panel -->
    <string name="about_row01">Owl SMS</string>
    <string name="about_row02">
        \nThis application makes information requests, directly to the Twilio REST APIs, to send, receive, manage messages, and retrieve the list of the account\'s SMS capable phone numbers.
        \n
        \nTo use Owl SMS, you are required to have Twilio account with at least one SMS capable phone number.
        \n
        \nGo to http://Twilio.com/console to get, and manage, your account.
        \n
        \nYou can use a free Twilio Trial account with Owl SMS. However, take note of the free Trial account restrictions. For example, you can only send and receive messages, to and from, phone numbers you have pre-verified. For more information on a Trial account, search for \"How does Twilio\'s Free Trial work?\"
        \n
    </string>
    <string name="about_row03">
        Owl SMS is offered \"as is\", without warrantee or guarantee.
    </string>
    <string name="about_row04">
        \nVersion: 0.6
        \nRelease date: October 31, 2017
        \n
        \nThis application is not a Twilio company application, even though it was developed by Twilio employees. There is a saying within the company, "Just draw the Owl." This is our drawing of an SMS application.
        \n
    </string>
    <!-- \n Draw the Owl: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dwSe2imUyvg -->

